    "description": "A barracks of the seventh cohort of the Vigiles, Rome's urban fire brigade, was located in the Transtiberim.",
    "details": "<p>Excavations carried out in 1865 in the De Romanis gardens in Trastevere exposed the barracks. Pietro Visconti carried out the excavations. In 1966, the archaeological area was consolidated and conserved.</p>",
